          "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nSB Docs renders the markup inside of JSDoc comments when it shouldn't. \r\n\r\nFor this JSDoc comment: \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/263385/84196897-ef87cb80-aa6e-11ea-9854-09c9493405c3.png)\r\n\r\nSBDocs' PropTable renders the real markup for `<a>` and `<button>`. When it should output the string instead.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/263385/84197011-2bbb2c00-aa6f-11ea-886d-10d36ebe6f85.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to SB Design System storybook [here](https://5ccbc373887ca40020446347-frgogtvejg.chromatic.com/?path=/docs/design-system-button--basic)\r\n2. Scroll down to `isLink`\r\n4. See that an empty `<button>` is added to the DOM \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nSB Docs should output the string instead. When I comment `<button>` in JSDocs should render as `<button>` in SB Docs instead of laying down a real DOM element.\r\n\r\n"
