          "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nFor React components which returns portal `addon-docs` this plugin won't create props table.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Create sample component which returns portal:\r\n```\r\n  return isOpen && createPortal(<div>{children}</div>, el);\r\n```\r\n2. Add some propTypes\r\n3. Add it to story \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nProps should be correctly shown in props table. Instead, \"No props found for this component\" is shown.\r\n\r\n**System:**\r\n```\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: macOS 10.15.4\r\n    CPU: (4) x64 Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-7360U CPU @ 2.30GHz\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 14.2.0 - /usr/local/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.4 - /usr/local/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 6.14.4 - /usr/local/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 81.0.4044.138\r\n    Firefox: 76.0.1\r\n    Safari: 13.1\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    @storybook/addon-actions: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/addon-docs: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/addon-knobs: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/addon-links: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/addon-viewport: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/addons: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n    @storybook/preset-create-react-app: ^2.1.1 => 2.1.1 \r\n    @storybook/react: ^5.3.18 => 5.3.18 \r\n```\r\n"
